What is derived
---------------
The include/ctll/ directory (the CTLL compile-time LL(1) parser,
ctll::fixed_string and supporting headers) is copied from notre, where
it descends from Hana Dusikova's CTRE with modifications. The build and
packaging scaffolding follows the sibling projects compile-time-json,
compile-time-json5 and compile-time-xml
(https://github.com/alexios-angel/). The YAML grammar, document types,
binder and the ctyaml API are original to this repository, but follow
the architecture CTRE established (a Tablewright-generated LL(1) table
driven by CTLL with semantic actions building a type-level result).

The parse table include/ctlark/lark.hpp is generated from
include/ctlark/lark.gram by Tablewright
(https://github.com/alexios-angel/Tablewright).

Attribution for the parser architecture and the CTLL engine belongs to
Hana Dusikova; this file preserves it as required by Section 4(c) of
the Apache License 2.0.

The grammar layer is ctlark
(https://github.com/alexios-angel/compile-time-lark), vendored under
include/ctlark/: the YAML grammar is written in the Lark grammar
language, designed by Erez Shinan and the lark-parser project
(https://github.com/lark-parser/lark, MIT license); see ctlark's
NOTICE for the full lineage.

YAML is a trademark-free specification by the YAML project
(https://yaml.org); ctyaml implements a documented subset of YAML 1.2
with the core schema.
